### **iOffer AI Agent**

#### **Phase 1: Foundation and Baseline Implementation**

This initial phase focuses on setting up the technical infrastructure and core agent framework.

* **Technology Stack:**  
  * The core framework will be built using Autogen for multi-agent conversations and Chainlit for the user interface.  
  * It is strongly recommended to use a model like Gemini-Flash for the Orchestration Agent to ensure speed and efficiency in routing user requests.  
* **Development Environment:**  
  * For initial debugging, each engineer can implement their agent in a unique Autogen \+ Chainlit environment.  
  * **Enhancement:** It is critically recommended to establish a unified and standardized development environment early in the process to mitigate future integration challenges and ensure seamless agent communication.  
* **Baseline Evaluation:**  
  * A comprehensive evaluation suite will be developed to test the baseline model's performance. This will include an out-of-sample validation dataset for predefined questions to test the General Q\&A Agent.

---

#### **Phase 2: Core Agent Development (Parallel Tasks)**

The development of the individual agents can proceed in parallel, with each agent having an enhanced set of responsibilities.

**1\. Orchestration Agent** The central coordinator of the user experience.

* **Core Functions:** Greet the user , manage handoffs to other specialized agents , and provide conversation summaries.  
* **Enhanced Capabilities:**  
  * **Goal Clarification:** Before extensive data collection, the agent will initiate a dialogue to clarify the student's primary goals (e.g., career-focused, research-oriented).  
  * **Contextual Handoffs:** When transferring a user to a professional consultant, the agent will provide a complete summary of the user's profile and conversation history to ensure a seamless transition.  
  * **Dynamic Context Management:** The agent will actively manage the conversation's context, summarizing past user interactions to ensure continuity.

**2\. Data Extraction Agent** Responsible for building and updating the student's profile.

* **Core Functions:** Prompt users to upload information via conversation or PDF files , handle key information extraction , upload raw data to the server , and check the database for pre-existing student information.  
* **Enhanced Capabilities:**  
  * **Conversational Data Gathering:** Instead of relying only on uploads, the agent will engage the user in a guided conversation to populate the student profile JSON, making the process more interactive.  
  * **Proactive Information Requests:** When information is missing, the agent will explain *why* it is needed (e.g., "Providing your GPA for the last two years helps us better assess your academic trend for competitive programs").  
  * **Automated Triggers:** The agent will dynamically trigger background functions, such as student profile analysis or school selection, as sufficient information becomes available.

![][image1]

**3\. Student Profile Assessment Agent** Provides students with an analysis of their academic and extracurricular standing.

* **Core Function:** Rank the student's strengths and weaknesses and present them in a visual format.  
* **Enhanced Capabilities:**  
  * **Narrative Assessment:** The agent will generate a qualitative, narrative report alongside the visual ranking. For example, "Your high quantitative scores make you a strong candidate for engineering programs, while gaining more research experience would strengthen your profile for top-tier universities."  
  * **Comparative Analysis:** The assessment will show how the student's profile compares to the average admitted student at their target schools, providing clear context to their competitiveness.

![][image2]

**4\. School Recommendation Agent** Delivers personalized school suggestions.

* **Core Function:** Generate a list of 3 reach, 4 target, and 3 safe schools.  
* **Enhanced Capabilities:**  
  * **Detailed Rationale:** Every recommendation will be accompanied by a justification that explains *why* the school is a good match, referencing specific aspects of the student's profile.  
  * **Feedback-Driven Refinement:** After presenting the initial list, the agent will ask for user feedback ("Are these schools in your preferred budget range?") and regenerate the list based on the user's input.  
  * **Hybrid Selection Model:** The agent will use an initial KNN model for a broad selection of schools, which can be further refined using more advanced RAG techniques.

![][image3]

**5\. General Question and Answering Agent** Acts as a knowledge base for common questions.

* **Core Function:** Answer student questions regarding the admission process.  
* **Plan:** Use Autogen Web surfer to find and extract basic information of that specific school/program. Then using RAG to fulfill and customize based on student  characteristics.   
* **Enhanced Capabilities:**  
  * **RAG Implementation:** This agent will be built with a Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) approach, connected to a database of school policies and admission requirements to ensure answers are accurate and up-to-date.

---

#### **Phase 3: Workflow Integration and Evaluation**

This phase focuses on ensuring all agents work together cohesively within the defined user workflow.

* **User Journey:** The workflow will follow the outlined process: User Login \-\> Agent Welcome \-\> Guided Data Collection \-\> Intent Recognition \-\> Handoff to Specialist Agent (School Rec, Q\&A) or Human Consultant.  
* **Comprehensive Evaluation:** A multi-faceted evaluation strategy will be implemented, measuring:  
  * **Data Extraction Accuracy:** How accurately the JSON profile is populated from user input.  
  * **Recommendation Relevance:** The quality and accuracy of school recommendations.  
  * **Intent Recognition Accuracy:** The success rate of the Orchestration Agent in routing users correctly.  
  * **User Satisfaction:** Qualitative feedback from test users on the helpfulness and ease of use of the system.

---

#### **Future Work**

* **Emotional Intelligence:** Future iterations will focus on optimizing the Orchestration Agent for higher emotional intelligence (EQ) in its responses to create a more supportive user experience.

### **iOffer AI Agent Project Timeline (6-Week Plan)**

---

#### **Week 1: Foundation and Initial Setup**

* **Objective:** Establish the project's technical foundation and finalize the development framework.  
* **Tasks:**  
  * Set up the core infrastructure using Autogen and Chainlit.  
  * Establish a standardized development environment for all engineers.  
  * Select and integrate the baseline LLM (e.g., Gemini-Flash) for the Orchestration Agent.  
  * Finalize the detailed JSON schema for the student profile based on the provided template.  
  * Develop the initial version of the evaluation test for the baseline model.

---

#### **Weeks 2-4: Parallel Agent Development**

* **Objective:** Develop the core functionalities of all five AI agents simultaneously.  
* **Tasks (to be worked on in parallel):**  
  * **Orchestration Agent:**  
    * Implement welcome messages and handoff logic to other agents.  
    * Develop context management and conversation summarization capabilities.  
  * **Data Extraction Agent:**  
    * Build functionality to process user uploads (PDFs/conversation) and extract key information.  
    * Implement logic to check the existing database for student information and request missing data.  
    * Develop dynamic function triggers for profile and school analysis.  
  * **Student Profile Assessment Agent:**  
    * Create the system to rank and visualize student strengths and weaknesses.  
    * Design the user interface for the comprehensive competitiveness score report, similar to the provided example.  
  * **School Recommendation Agent:**  
    * Implement the initial school selection model (e.g., KNN).  
    * Develop the logic to generate a list of 3 reach, 4 target, and 3 safe schools with scoring.  
  * **General Q\&A Agent:**  
    * Set up the RAG pipeline with a vector database for answering questions on admission processes.  
    * Create the out-of-sample validation dataset with predefined questions.

---

#### **Week 5: Integration, Workflow, and User Interface**

* **Objective:** Integrate the developed agents and build the end-to-end user workflow.  
* **Tasks:**  
  * Integrate all five agents into a single, cohesive application.  
  * Implement the user workflow as detailed in the flowchart, focusing on intent recognition and agent handoffs.  
  * Build the UI for agent interaction, displaying the "Agent thinking process" where applicable.  
  * Implement the mechanism for transferring the user to a professional study abroad consultant.  
  * Conduct initial end-to-end testing of the integrated system.

---

#### **Week 6: Evaluation, Refinement, and Deployment**

* **Objective:** Rigorously test the complete system, refine its performance, and prepare for deployment.  
* **Tasks:**  
  * Execute the full evaluation suite, measuring data extraction accuracy, recommendation relevance, and Q\&A correctness.  
  * Analyze test results and perform bug fixing and performance tuning across all agents.  
  * Refine agent prompts and RAG retrieval strategies based on evaluation outcomes.  
  * Finalize all UI elements, including the school recommendation cards and profile reports.  
  * Prepare for deployment.

### **Autogen** 

I strongly recommend playing around the Autogen studio. Definition of Agents is similar to other services like openai agent sdk, but does provide some interesting concepts like reflect\_on\_too\_use. Used in production in small startups and large enterprises. There is a recent update from 0.2 to 0.4. 

Doc Link (0.2) Contains good information on key concepts: [https://microsoft.github.io/autogen/0.2/docs/Getting-Started](https://microsoft.github.io/autogen/0.2/docs/Getting-Started)

Doc Link (0.4) updated version: [https://microsoft.github.io/autogen/stable/user-guide/agentchat-user-guide/migration-guide.html](https://microsoft.github.io/autogen/stable/user-guide/agentchat-user-guide/migration-guide.html)

Examples (0.2):  
[https://microsoft.github.io/autogen/0.2/docs/Examples/\#automated-multi-agent-chat](https://microsoft.github.io/autogen/0.2/docs/Examples/#automated-multi-agent-chat)

Examples (0.4):  
[https://github.com/microsoft/autogen/tree/main/python/samples](https://github.com/microsoft/autogen/tree/main/python/samples)

Chainlit integration   
[https://github.com/microsoft/autogen/tree/main/python/samples/agentchat\_chainlit](https://github.com/microsoft/autogen/tree/main/python/samples/agentchat_chainlit)
